The article discusses the comprehensive energy security strategy announced by the Obama administration. The strategy includes expanding domestic production of oil and gas in the Outer Continental Shelf (OCS) to increase energy independence while protecting marine areas. It also includes historic fuel efficiency standards for vehicles, efforts to improve energy security in the Department of Defense, and a push for a greener federal vehicle fleet. The article provides background information on each of these initiatives and highlights their importance in transitioning to a clean energy economy.